ign uncertainty of the state of each individual, and\nconsequently optimize the testing as to reduce the overall uncertainty given a\nconstrained testing budget. These tools can also be used to optimize vaccine\ndistribution to curb the disease spread when limited vaccines are available. We\npresent a few simulation results that illustrate the performance of the\nproposed framework, and estimate the impact of incomplete contact tracing data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Sep 2020 16:24:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Sep 2020 14:22:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 16 Oct 2020 21:18:48 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 10 Sep 2021 16:37:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-13"}
